Fore wing (Fig. 2
d-f
). Forewing longer than body, wing margin with long cilia; radial cell 4.3 times as long as the wide, partially closed (R1 vein projected about 1/3-1/2 on radial cell margin), Rs and R1 veins slightly curved, areolet distinct; vein Rs+M distinct, nearly reaching basalis.
